fix: honest reconciliation narrative + real user_instructions filter

Three bugs found by the user on the same deployed catalog view:

1. "FROM —" on every reconciliation card.
   The production reconciliation code (reconciliation.py) never
   populated left_name/right_name/left_source_id/right_source_id on
   the ReconciliationResult. Only the fixture cockpit carried them,
   so every real run rendered as "Candidate A from — → Candidate B
   from —". Fixed via a single _pair_display_fields helper spread
   into every return site (6 code paths).

2. Reconciliation layer shown on single-source runs.
   The cross-source narrative only makes sense when there are at
   least 2 sources AND at least one actually cross-source pair. On
   a single-source run it was pure noise and broke the product's
   value story (the hero is the dish graph + aliases + search, not
   the reconciliation meta-layer). Both the Cockpit narrative and
   the Processing live panel now return null unless there is a real
   cross-source pair to talk about.

3. "no veggie" in user_instructions was ignored by Opus.
   The directive used to ship as a polite trailer block AFTER the
   generic "extract dishes" directive, phrased as "apply them on top
   of the rules". Opus 4.7 treated it as a nice-to-have. Now the
   block ships FIRST (right after the image, before the generic
   directive) and in imperative hard-filter wording: "DROPPED from
   the output entirely", "Drop silently", "apply the most
   restrictive reasonable reading". The system prompt was also
   amended with a new protocol rule (#4) that names the HARD FILTER
   block explicitly so the model knows what to look for.

Tests added:
- test_reconciliation_display: every code path of
  reconcile_deterministic carries display fields.
- test_extraction_user_instructions updated to lock in the new
  ordering and hard-filter tone.

84/84 backend tests pass, frontend build clean, 0 lint errors.
